column5: just heard on the news a 40 car crash just occurred. Might want to re-think your route if heading north for the weekend. ( i will be )  1 death reported
http://www.thestar.com/news/article/926092--one-dead-as-multi-vehicle-crash-closes-hwy-11?bn=1  Definitely changed my plans until tomorrow am at least.
Happened back around 11/11:30 am.  Leah and her sister tried every route/back road and cow path at 9am this morning..to try to get down to Barrie to shop.. Came home with the credit card bill BLANK!
tragic for sure .good defensive driving would have avoided this scenario.
If you look long enough and hard enough, there is always an upside to every downside
they weren't in it is also pretty upside.........somehow with a weekend comin', I think Irish still has a bill a'comin

Driving up to work in Penetang today at 8 am was bad.  Real bad.  I could see about 20 yards in front of me.  It was the same snowfall that caused that mess.  The lady should not have gotten out of her car.  Too bad.  That is not nice.
